<h1 align="center">ColdFusion Studio Instructions</h1>

<p align="left">The following instructions apply for users of ColdFusion Studio.
In order to use Studio, the end-user should have an host address, user id
and&nbsp; password.&nbsp;</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p align="left">Studio will make an FTP connection to the web server and
    will allow you to create, update and delete pages on the server.&nbsp;</li>
  <li>
    <p align="left">You cannot, however, rename files. To rename files you will
    need to use an FTP program. You could, however open a file, save it with the
    new name and delete the old file.</li>
  <li>
    <p align="left">To test your pages you still need to use a web browser.</li>
</ul>
<h4 align="left">Configuring a FTP Connection</h4>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p align="left">Run Cold Fusion Studio</li>
  <li>
    <p align="left">Click on the <b>Remote Files </b>tab</li>
</ul>
<p align="center"><img border="0" src="images/Cfsfig07.gif" align="center" width="272" height="257"></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p align="left">Right Click on <b>Remote Servers</b> and select <b>Add FTP
    Server</b></li>
  <li>
    <p align="left">In the <i>Configure FTP Server </i>dialog, enter a
    description, host name and initial directory (if needed) and click OK</li>
</ul>
<p align="center"><img border="0" src="images/Cfsfig02.gif" width="482" height="361"></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p align="left">The new server connection will display in the window, click
    on the new connection. A dialog <i>Login failed </i>window will appear,
    enter the username and passwords provided by your professor.</li>
</ul>
<p align="center"><img border="0" src="images/Cfsfig03.gif" width="267" height="145"></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p align="left">Click on the <b>&quot;+&quot; </b>sign to the left of the
    connection, you will see the directories under the server description. You
    will also see the list of files in the current directory in the window
    below.</li>
</ul>
<p align="center"><img border="0" src="images/Cfsfig04.gif" width="788" height="400"></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p align="left">To open a file, just click on the file name, the code will
    appear in the right window.</li>
  <li>
    <p align="left">To save your changes, click on <b>File | Save </b>or in the
    disk icon in the toolbar.</li>
</ul>
<p align="center"><img border="0" src="images/Cfsfig06.gif" width="384" height="72"></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <p align="left">To create a new file, just click on new in the toolbar, or <b>File
    | New </b>to get a list of templates to use.</li>
</ul>
